1. Purpose
This project is a simple library website allowing users to:
Register an account
Log in / log out
Reserve books
Un-reserve books
2. Technologies Used
PHP (backend)
MySQL or similar database (via db.php)
HTML + CSS for frontend
Basic session / authentication logic
3. Setup Instructions
Clone the repository.
Set up a local web server (e.g., XAMPP, WAMP, LAMP) with PHP and MySQL.
Import or create the database schema (not documented here).
In db.php, update the database credentials (host, username, password, database name).
Place the project in the web server’s root (e.g., htdocs or www).
Access via browser, e.g., http://localhost/Library-Website/index.html.
4. File Structure (key files)
index.html — Welcome / landing page.
registration.php — Handles user registration with form validation.
login.php — Handles user login with session management.
login_homepage.php — User's homepage after login with navigation links.
reservation.php — Book reservation interface with search by title and category browsing (Health, Business, Biography, Technology, Travel, Self-Help, Cookery, Fiction).
logout.php — Handles user logout and session destruction.
db.php — Database connection file (connects to 'Bookdb' database on localhost).
main.css — Styling.
viewreg.php — Displays the logged-in user's reserved books and allows unreserving them.
usernotloged.html — Page prompting users to log in before reserving books.
test_reserve_form.html — Test form for book reservation (development/testing).
